Antennule (Fig. 1a) extending to about 0.4 times length of carapace. Peduncle 4-articulate (Fig. 2a), article 1 short, 0.2 times length of article 2, naked. Article 2, three times as long as wide with two plumose setae on mid-anterior margin, row of six plumose setae on lateral margin and 13 setae antero-distally. Article 3 half length of article 2, slightly longer than wide with two setae on disto-lateral margin and an antero-distal cluster of setae. Article 4, 0.7 times length of article 3, width same as length, with one distal stout spine, two rows each of four setae on inner lateral margin near spine. Outer lateral margin with two setae and long distal seta behind the scale. Antennular scale elliptical (Fig. 2
a'
), 2.5 times as long as wide, with rows of setae on anterior distal margin. Antennular flagellum slightly longer than peduncle and composed of 10 articles.

